dent of abandoning his commitment to human rights. Trapped in this contradiction, Carter lost both the opportunity to renew détente and to build lasting domestic support.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDetentexHistoryy20th century. 0aHuman rightszSoviet Union. 4aInternational Relations 2020. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh  aAmerican foreign policy.  aCold War.  aCongress.  aDétente.  aHuman rights.  aJimmy Carter.  aNeoconservatives.  aSoviet Dissent.  aSoviet Union.  aZbigniew Brzezinski.  aneoconservatives.1 aTulli, Umberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614603840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526146038423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526146038/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles